reviews.text: Ordered delivery from this restaurant for the first time tonight. I was craving an Italian sub but this was 110% NOT the place for it.  Not only did they ignore my topping request and charge extra for provolone, the bread was soggy when it arrived only 20 minutes later. Impressive. Side note: Don't order coke if you actually want coke like the menu says.  They only carry Pepsi products.   The delivery person was very nice and found my home easily for a relatively quick delivery on a Saturday night. Overall, this place was way overpriced for the low quality food I received.  Only giving 1 star for the lovely delivery person and the bag of lays that was supposed to be cape cod. üôÑ

detailedReviews.author: Geoff Goselin
detailedReviews.text: Found this place passing thru Arlington on a road trip and ordered a hot smoked turkey and a warmed Italian to go. 30 minutes later on the freeway to New Jersey, we bit into the best tasting bread we‚Äôve ever had on a sando. The first thing you taste on a sandwich is the bread so it needs be tasty not like Subway. Arlington Cafe has nailed the taste and texture and only wish we had dined in so I could have complimented them in person. Being a pizza place too, I suspect they make their own bread. Only problem now, is when back in California, all sandos will forever need meet the bar set by the Arlington Cafe. HaZah!
